        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): run daily session resets on schedule",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Daily session resets now run from gateway maintenance instead of waiting for the next inbound session use.\n- The scheduler scans configured session stores and calls the existing reset service for stale daily sessions after the configured boundary.\n- The maintenance timer now reads current runtime config on each sweep, so hot config changes to `session.reset`, `session.resetByType`, `session.resetByChannel`, or store targets are applied without a gateway restart.\n- Docs now describe proactive daily rollover and the implicit provider-owned CLI session exemption.\n\n## Linked context\n\n- Closes #82321\n- Related PRs or discussions: none known beyond the review conversation on this PR.\n- Maintainer or owner request: not separately requested; this addresses the filed daily session reset bug.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Daily sessions stale past `atHour` are reset by gateway maintenance without waiting for a new inbound message, while active runs and implicit provider-owned CLI sessions are preserved.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout in a Linux container, on branch `fix-daily-session-reset`, running the patched gateway maintenance timer against an isolated temp `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`. Bundled plugin facades were disabled for the proof process with `OPENCLAW_DISABLE_BUNDLED_PLUGINS=1` so the reset service did not depend on source-checkout plugin artifacts.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  - Ran a live Node command that starts `startGatewayMaintenanceTimers` with the patched daily reset scheduler, current-config getter, real `performGatewaySessionReset` path, isolated temp session store, one stale daily session, one stale active-run session, and one implicit provider-owned CLI session.\n  - Command shape: `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=<tmp> OPENCLAW_DISABLE_BUNDLED_PLUGINS=1 node --import tsx - <<'TS' ... startGatewayMaintenanceTimers(...) ... TS`\n  - Supplemental verification: `./node_modules/.bin/vitest run src/gateway/session-daily-reset-scheduler.test.ts src/gateway/server-maintenance.test.ts --config test/vitest/vitest.gateway.config.ts`\n  - Supplemental type gates: `pnpm check:test-types && pnpm tsgo:prod`\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output):\n  ```text\n  $ OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=<tmp> OPENCLAW_DISABLE_BUNDLED_PLUGINS=1 node --import tsx - <<'TS'\n  # creates isolated agents/main/sessions/sessions.json\n  # starts patched gateway maintenance timers\n  # waits for daily reset sweep to invoke the real reset service\n  TS\n  gateway-proof: before {\"stale\":\"old-regular-session\",\"active\":\"old-active-session\",\"cli\":\"old-cli-session\"}\n  [session-daily-reset] daily session reset sweep complete\n  gateway-proof: after {\"stale\":\"5f959c12-f0ed-4ed1-99d2-cc158c66ac87\",\"active\":\"old-active-session\",\"cli\":\"old-cli-session\"}\n  gateway-proof: staleReset true\n  gateway-proof: activePreserved true\n  gateway-proof: implicitCliPreserved true\n\n  $ ./node_modules/.bin/vitest run src/gateway/session-daily-reset-scheduler.test.ts src/gateway/server-maintenance.test.ts --config test/vitest/vitest.gateway.config.ts\n  Test Files  2 passed (2)\n  Tests       18 passed (18)\n\n  $ pnpm check:test-types && pnpm tsgo:prod\n  exit_code=0\n  ```\n- Observed result after fix: The running gateway maintenance timer reset the stale daily session through the actual reset service without any inbound message. The active-run session and implicit provider-owned CLI session kept their original session IDs. Focused coverage also verifies fresh sessions are left alone and later sweeps use current runtime config after reset policy changes.\n- What was not tested: A multi-hour live gateway wait that naturally crosses the configured reset hour.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: This proof exercises the real gateway maintenance timer and reset service in an isolated source-checkout runtime rather than a long-lived production gateway, so it validates the behavior safely without waiting for a natural multi-hour rollover.\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): Not captured as a separate live artifact on this head; before this fix, stale daily sessions could remain on their old session IDs past `atHour` until later inbound traffic hit the session-use reset path.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- Commands run:\n  - CI=true COREPACK_HOME=<workspace>/.corepack node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/gateway/server-close.test.ts src/gateway/server-maintenance.test.ts src/gateway/server-runtime-services.test.ts src/gateway/server-startup-post-attach.test.ts src/gateway/server.sessions.reset-hooks.test.ts src/gateway/session-daily-reset-scheduler.test.ts\n  - CI=true COREPACK_HOME=<workspace>/.corepack pnpm -s check:test-types\n  - CI=true COREPACK_HOME=<workspace>/.corepack pnpm test:channels\n  - git diff --check after resolving the current upstream/main merge\n  - git merge --no-edit upstream/main, resolved server-close/session-reset conflicts, then pushed head 1fb0ade39f\n- Regression coverage added or updated: src/gateway/session-daily-reset-scheduler.test.ts, src/gateway/server-maintenance.test.ts, and src/gateway/server.sessions.reset-hooks.test.ts.\n- Locked-in scenarios: stale daily reset without inbound traffic, fresh-session no-op, active-run skip, implicit provider-owned CLI skip, hot config reload for future sweeps, overlapping sweep skip, shutdown cleanup, and selected-row race protection.\n- What failed before this fix: daily reset staleness was only evaluated through session-use paths, so stale sessions could survive past atHour until later inbound traffic.\n- If no test was added, why not? Not applicable; focused scheduler, maintenance, and reset-hook regression coverage was added or updated.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- Did user-visible behavior change? (Yes/No) Yes. Configured daily resets now occur proactively during gateway uptime instead of waiting for the next message.\n- Did config, environment, or migration behavior change? (Yes/No) No.\n- Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (Yes/No) No.\n- Highest-risk area: session-state compatibility for deployments that implicitly depended on lazy daily reset timing.\n- Mitigation: the new behavior matches the configured wall-clock daily reset contract; the scheduler skips active runs, preserves implicit provider-owned CLI sessions under the default policy, avoids overlapping sweeps, and reloads current config before each sweep.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- Next action: ClawSweeper and maintainers can re-review the refreshed branch at head 1fb0ade39f.\n- Still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof: no known author-side action remains; CI/checks may still need to settle after the upstream refresh push.\n- Bot or reviewer comments addressed: the branch is now current with upstream/main. The merge kept upstream agent-aware reset behavior, preserved the daily selected-row race guard, updated the scheduler import for the normalization package move, and retained shutdown cleanup for the daily reset interval.\n- Latest local validation on refreshed head: focused gateway reset/shutdown suite passed with 14 files and 292 tests; check:test-types passed; test:channels passed with 70 files and 650 tests; git diff --check passed.\n",
